The paper deals with fine-grained entity type classification using neural network models and distant supervision paradigm. This falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel approach to jointly learn entity mentions and their context representation, which involves the use of embeddings. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of transfer learning to improve the performance of FETC systems, which could make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
